Rev. Freeman said many of the females endured 'tremendous trauma' in the book and said: 'We are just finally finding out their stories.' 

She told the Huffington Post: 'We have for whatever reason overlooked the witness of women in the Bible for all these thousands of years and all the contributions they've made to the faith and to world history.  

'We have cried over these stories, we have laughed over these stories. Our faith has been increased.' 

