The Bible does contain references to when women should be allowed to speak, and one interpretation of 1 Corinthians, suggests Paul wrote that women "should remain silent" while in church.

Rev. Freeman is an expert on the subject of female roles in the Holy Book and is also the author of 'The Scarlet Cord: Conversations With God's Chosen Women' which studied the stories of 12 women in the Bible. 

Their findings have been published in a book called 'Bible Women: All Their Words and Why They Matter'. 

 

